    <!-- Security Architecture -->
    <section id="architecture" class="mt-24 lg:mt-32 scroll-mt-24">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
        <h2 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-gray-900 sm:text-4xl">Security architecture</h2>
        <p class="mt-4 text-base text-gray-600 leading-7">How OneUptime is engineered to keep customer data isolated, encrypted, and recoverable.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-12 grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">Encryption</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">All data encrypted at rest using AES-256. All data in transit secured with TLS 1.2 or TLS 1.3 only; older protocols disabled. Customer-managed keys (BYOK) available for enterprise via AWS KMS, Azure Key Vault, GCP KMS, or HashiCorp Vault.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">Tenant isolation</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Logical isolation by Project ID enforced at API, database, and storage layers. Optional physical isolation: dedicated database, dedicated namespace, dedicated object-storage bucket, and dedicated keys per tenant.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">Identity and access</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">SAML 2.0 and OpenID Connect SSO. SCIM 2.0 user provisioning. MFA enforceable at tenant level (TOTP, WebAuthn). Role-based access control with custom roles and per-resource scoping.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">Network and infrastructure</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Hosted on tier-1 cloud providers (AWS, Azure, GCP) in customer-pinned regions. WAF, DDoS protection, and IP allowlisting on admin endpoints. Bastion-only access for production, gated through SSO + MFA.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">Data residency</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Region pinning at the project level. Available regions include US-East, US-West, EU-West, EU-Central, AP-Southeast, AP-Northeast, and CA-Central. Backups stay in-region. <a href="/legal/data-residency" class="text-gray-900 underline underline-offset-2">More on data residency &rarr;</a></p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">Audit logging</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Immutable, tenant-scoped audit logs cover admin actions, incident state changes, schedule changes, role changes, integration secret changes, login events, and data exports. Exportable to your SIEM.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">Secure development</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">Mandatory peer review, signed commits, automated SAST and dependency scanning on every pull request, SBOM published per release, and supply-chain attestations via SLSA Level 3.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="rounded-xl bg-white p-6 ring-1 ring-gray-200">
          <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-gray-900">Open source by design</h3>
          <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">The entire platform is open source on <a href="https://github.com/oneuptime/oneuptime" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="text-gray-900 underline underline-offset-2">GitHub</a>. Customers can audit the code, run it self-hosted, and verify security claims independently.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

